ner" itemprop=3D"text">
         =20

<p>How to easily convert a Celsius temperature into Fahrenheit temperature =
in your head?</p>



<p>Sometimes you see a Celsius temperature and you don=E2=80=99t always hav=
e a unit converter quickly available. Don=E2=80=99t worry, this conversion =
is not that complicated, let me explain to you how to do that quickly in yo=
ur head.</p>



<p>We do this conversion in two steps:</p>



<p><strong>Step 1</strong>: One degree of =C2=B0C equals 1.8 =C2=B0F. (Or i=
t is 9/5, but I think 1.8 is easier to think). Yep, I know that multiplying=
 with 1.8 in your head is not that easy, but there is a pretty easy way aro=
und this: multiply the =C2=B0C reading first with 2 (easy) and then take of=
f 10% (also easy).</p>



<p><strong>Step 2</strong>: You need to remember that 0 =C2=B0C equals 32 =
=C2=B0F, remember that! So, finally, ad that 32 =C2=B0F offset to the resul=
t.</p>



<p><strong>Let=E2=80=99s take some examples</strong>:</p>



<p>What is 20 =C2=B0C in F=C2=B0?</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Multiply 20 by 2 =3D 40.</li>



<li>Remove 10 % from 40 =3D 40 =E2=80=93 4 =3D 36.</li>



<li>Add 32 =C2=B0F offset to that 36 + 32 =C2=B0F =3D 68 =C2=B0F.</li>



<li>So, 20 =C2=B0C equals 68 =C2=B0F. Pretty easy, right?</li>
</ul>



<p>What is 100 =C2=B0C in =C2=B0F?</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Multiply 100 by 2 =3D 200.</li>



<li>Remove 10 % from 200 =3D 200 =E2=80=93 20 =3D 180.</li>



<li>Add 32 =C2=B0F offset to that 180 + 32 =C2=B0F =3D 212 =C2=B0F.</li>



<li>So, 100 =C2=B0C equals 212 =C2=B0F.</li>
</ul>



<p>What is 0 =C2=B0C in =C2=B0F?</p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Well, that is 32 =C2=B0F. I told you to remember that, didn=E2=80=99t I=
=E2=80=A6</li>
</ul>



<p>The =E2=80=9C<strong>quick and dirty</strong>=E2=80=9D way would be just=
 to multiply the Celsius reading by 2 and add 32 =C2=B0F. But that will giv=
e a bit too high results, so take the end results down a bit. For the above=
 example of 20 =C2=B0C, this would give 20 x 2 + 32 =3D 72 =C2=B0F. Sure it=
 gives you a rough value, but as you can see the result will be a bit too h=
igh.</p>


